{'artwork_url': 'https://i1.sndcdn.com/artworks-000442524075-cy63kt-large.jpg', 'caption': None, 'commentable': True, 'comment_count': 12, 'created_at': '2018-11-19T14:46:52Z', 'description': '"What's in a name?" asked Shakespeare a few centuries back. "That which we call a rose by any other word would smell as sweet," continued the poet. Well, when one listens to Birds Ov Paradise, the answer to old Willie's classic question is actually "Everything". It's rare to hear an artist with such clarity of vision and singularity of purpose; it's even more precious to have the artist's moniker almost define that vision. Pick any track from Birds ov Paradise and you'll hear birds in it. No, not a happy bird chirping in the background, but a litany of reverberated, occasionally rhythmic and occasionally chaotic percussive whispers, pokes, ticks and tacks, that indeed sound like a fluttering of wings. Sometimes those sounds resemble a flock of birds happily flying around a park on a sunny day; sometimes the birds are creating a menacing sense of tension straight out of Hitchcock, and sometimes the sounds channel somber darkness of ravens circling an old oak tree in a dark forest in the gray of twilight. "Wild Growth" leans towards the light rather than darkness. And with it's stronger sense of melodic purpose and benign ambiance, it sounds more like an early morning of what will turn out to be a sunny day, with minimalistic "birds" ambiance providing a sense ease and hope rather than gloom that's prevalent on many other tracks from the artist. It's another gem in the artist's library and clearly an original in a landscape overflowing with too many derivative producers.

Savannah EP is coming out on November 23rd via Hypnus Records (https://soundcloud.com/hypnus)

'2019-05-01T12:32:43Z', 'description': 'The afternoon sun can be brutal in the summer. With your motionless body parked at the beach, it pounds and flattens you with ferocity and determination of an Italian grandma making veal Milanese. Sipping piña coladas brings no respite: the sun is too strong and you are too overheated and dehydrated. You are in a daze; it hurts to open your eyes and it hurts to keep them closed. The email notification sound from your phone slices your daze like a knife. What now?! "A new release", it says. "Why not?" you struggle to think. "Modern House Quintet", it says. "Why not?" Preview "Sunset", it says. "Why not?!" A lowering of the needle, a sip of warm piña colada with its own desperately melting ice and … "Sweet Jesus, I feel a breeze!" you jump. The sun now seems to be pouring itself down the distant horizon, releasing your body from its crosshair. You feel weightless; your body is still sluggish from the heat and piña coladas, but your spirit now moves with all the grace of a ballet dancer. 
It dances a happy dance, for "Sunset" is happy music. The rhythm is happy; the pads are happy and soothing; the track moves like a breeze and even the acid groove, that trademark tool of all things melancholic and trippy, is deftly controlled to bubble pleasantly in the background as the track takes flight.

SoHaSo is very happy to welcome an recently unknown entity on the label, Joannes is here with a fresh sound originating form the North of Holland. We all need to do shadow work once in a while, integrating our inner demons to create a more balanced reflection to carry out our lives from. The Got Needs EP provides the soundtrack for this personal journey, including delightful remixes by Nadia Struiwigh and Melatonin Man. 

Got Needs A1 is a powerful groove with heavily driven drum machines and 303 bassline for peak hour introspection, it doesn’t get more hypnotic than this. Melatonin Man strips down Joannes’ effort into a down-tempo electro affair containing some spell-binding rhythms that sure is to move some boo... 
On the B-side we find Joannes taking a more emotional approach, having pads and a cross rhythmic synth riff do the heavy lifting. Nadia Struiwigh takes these elements to the outer reaches of the universe. '2019-01-07T01:42:12Z', 'description': 'Blankstairs began as a series of all-ages DIY parties spawning from visual artists Nathaniel Young and Warren Mark Way. The events possessed a certain renegade and unhinged energy and, at the time, fulfilled their desire to engage with Portland’s music community.

The events were hosted in art galleries and whatever various alternative spaces were at the two’s disposal at the age of 19. Local visual artists were often presented on the same plane as the musical performances driving the events. In time, the pair found themselves surrounded by friends seeking a suitable platform for their visual and musical output, and thus the label was born.

The first release and compilation in July of 2013 presented a triad of subdued, stoned-out jams and somber ambient music, alongside club constructions of various shapes and sizes. Fast forwarding to the present finds Nathaniel and Warren both based out of New York and continuing to release music that represents the artists that are immediately involved in their lives –– the label being an expression of that which surrounds them.

In celebration of six years of operations Blankstairs is excited to issue a three part compilation featuring work from artists based in both spiritual homes for the label –– Cascadia and New York City, a selection that we feel is an accurate representation from Blankstairs friends and family both near and far.

https://soundcloud.com/aosseattle
www.blnkstrs.com

Illustration by Warren Mark Way & Nathaniel Young 
Design + Layout by Nathaniel Young 
Mastered by Matt Parent

returns with another strong addition to its Totem series, a unique set of releases pressed on transparent 10” vinyl, capturing the essence and effusiveness of multidimensionality of club culture. Bridging the gap between the worlds of sound and material objects, Totem is a series that aims to meld the artistic resonance of each forthcoming release into an emblematic representation of the sounds that are to be presented, clearly within the grooves seen and heard on the 10”. Stepping up for the third release in the series is Berlin legend Efdemin — bringing a three-track journey that is unequivocally enduring and flexible for journeys on-and-off the dancefloor.

While each track shares the same title, the textures and traits are different — with the A1, “Circles” setting things up with pertinent percussion and staccato synth lines; as Efdemin sways towards another side with “Left” — a heady, hedonistic thumper with exuberant melodic bursts; followed by a therapeutic sequel with “Right” — closing out the release with a melange of spacious efficacy, something the Berlin-based producer has been known for throughout his near-two-decade career. Between releasing for the likes of Ostgut Ton, Curle, Dial, and his own imprint Naïf; Efdemin takes on the challenge of Totem’s conceptual subjugation and subverts it with his emotionally honest take on a stimulating and subdural sonic experience within three parts. Narratively dense and expertly-paced, the Totem series carries on with another outer-worldly insertion to its catalog.

SoHaSo is very happy to welcome an recently unknown entity on the label, Joannes is here with a fresh sound originating form the North of Holland. We all need to do shadow work once in a while, integrating our inner demons to create a more balanced reflection to carry out our lives from. The Got Needs EP provides the soundtrack for this personal journey, including delightful remixes by Nadia Struiwigh and Melatonin Man. 

Got Needs A1 is a powerful groove with heavily driven drum machines and 303 bassline for peak hour introspection, it doesn’t get more hypnotic than this. Melatonin Man strips down Joannes’ effort into a down-tempo electro affair containing some spell-binding rhythms that sure is to move some boo... 
On the B-side we find Joannes taking a more emotional approach, having pads and a cross rhythmic synth riff do the heavy lifting. Nadia Struiwigh takes these elements to the outer reaches of the universe. Across 15 minutes, Efdemin’s experimental spirit is in full swing, with morphing drones/chords generated by a mix of Efdemin’s hurdy-gurdy and drum machines, Konrad Sprenger’s MIDI-controlled Stratocaster, Joachim Schütz’s electric guitar and Nika Son’s synthesizer – recorded live during the quartet’s Tony Conrad tribute concert in Hamburg. 

Album-wise, ‘New Atlantis’ oscillates between fast, kaleidoscopic techno, multilayered drones and acoustic instrumentation, fusing for the first time Sollmann’s deep dancefloor productions as Efdemin with his sound art and avant-garde music projects. The latter include 2017’s Harry Partch-inspired ‘Monophonie’ performance and 2018’s ‘Panama / Suez’ EP with Oren Ambarchi and Konrad Sprenger.

Sollmann took inspiration for ‘New Atlantis’ from Francis Bacon’s unfinished 17th century novel of the same name, which describes a fictional island devoted to social progress through the synthesis of art, science, technology and fashion.

Opposite to birds they fly with their hands, which implies already their scientific name Chiroptera. Bats have learned to hunt and to orientate even in absolute darkness. Since these waves are mostly in a frequency spectrum of 40 - 130 kHz, they are not perceptible to the human ear. With special bat detectors you can transform them however into our audible range. [{'artwork_url': 'https://i1.sndcdn.com/artworks-000128171775-ph8bb2-large.jpg', 'caption': None, 'commentable': True, 'comment_count': 63, 'created_at': '2015-09-01T15:12:04Z', 'description': 'Ahead of our showcase in Hamburg with Generator next week, Sofia Kourtesis has put together a mix paying homage to her adopted home. For more info on the show, and for RSVP – head here: http://boilerroom.tv/generator/hamburg/

"This mix is based on being in Hamburg, my current status and things that inspire me when I am here. I'm having a kind of nomadic life at the moment, but I think I could call Hamburg my home. The mix is about being at home and resting before a big fight – sometimes I need to be in a dark place or depressed mood to write or make music. I'm not an unhappy person, it's just easier to focus in such a mood."

–– Sofia Kourtesis

description:
We´re all just walking each other home.

Jose Padilla (4.12.1955 - 18.10.2020)
Ich habe ihn als sensiblen, komplexen Künstler voller Gegensätze in Erinnerung und bin sehr dankbar mit Ihm zusammen ein Stück seines musikalischen Schaffensweges gegangen zu sein.

Wenn man Jose Ehren möchte macht man das am besten an seinem Lieblings Strand Aguas Blancas mit einem guten Glas Wein und spricht einem Toast aus auf sein großes musikalisches Vermächtnis.

Release info:
"As the New Year appears, 2022 sees fresh music come into focus as Meanwhile Horizons welcomes Chris Zippel to the roster and his “Noosphere / Ombra” EP.
 
An iconic artist with a host of impressive production credentials to his name, Chris Zippel, has been at the vanguard of electronic music since the age of 15. His portfolio thus sees music writing credits for the Pet Shop Boys, Robbie Williams, Norah Jones and Paul Van Dyk in a long and illustrious career. Splitting his time between his Berlin hometown and the party island of Ibiza, Zippel also has a raft of solo production credits to his name, dating back to a debut for Organic Records in early 2001. Since then, a cornucopia of underground electronic music has found its way onto the likes of Elektrolux, Parasol Phonotheque, Ubersee Music and Allisum Records.
 
Now debuting on GMJ and Matter’s sister imprint, Chris Zippel opens with the spellbinding “Noosphere”. Anchored upon a thumping beat and ticking hi-hat percussion, a rolling groove is the perfect bedrock for a hypnotic analogue bassline to propel the track forwards, accompanied by a smooth arpeggio and sympathetic melodic phrasing. The result is a rare and emotive combination that arouses hairs on the back of the neck as “Noosphere” builds in unrelenting fashion to a rousing dénouement in the second half.
 
Continuing the rich melodic building blocks of its partner track, “Ombra” is a slightly more relaxed affair with its beautifully sculpted analogue envelopes that simultaneously harness the spirit of Jean Michel Jarre, Vangelis and Georgio Moroder. A gloriously filtered arpeggio meanders across proceedings as white noise crashes and ethereal chord sequences paint a vivid sonic picture, gradually revealing itself across an 8-minute timeframe, atop a sumptuous undulating groove.
 
Out of the shadows, Chris Zippel is able to harness a sublime musical evolution, illustrated by his “Noosphere / Ombra” EP."

30

ARTISTS Plagz
RELEASE DATE 2016-11-17
LABELS Bullfinch
CATALOG BF121


Passing the milestone of 30 years you much overestimate. You look at everything completely differently. Someone comes to this sooner, someone later. In music, I came to 30. My melancholy remains. My opinion, the vision and the desire to be "the other" is still in my tracks. Among white swans, for me, my music the rest of the world - the black swan.
In the new album, each track is deep emotions and feelings in my inner world. Every musician make its I and I am no exception.
Even the names of the tracks were chosen for a reason. This emotion, this association is thinking, feeling.
All the tracks of the album have one branch, one style, and even a set of synthesizers, moves, sounds and melodies. I did not think, I just wrote the senses. "Noise" - came out basis. But what kind of "noise"? Soul emotions of past days, experiences, let everyone understands in his own way, let everyone either finds or simply let go.

Mastering by Bullfinch Audio

Next up in our moments series we are very proud to share an amazing recent LIVE set from our label bosses GMJ & Matter at the Morning After presents: Enchanted Garden Homegrown Edition from April 2021! 

This set saw the boys premiering a number of new tunes alongside many live effects & synths in the moment! 

We hope you enjoy these moments!!


Melbourne’s GMJ (Gavin Martin) and Matter (Matty Doyle) joined forces in late 2015, a triggered recognition and magnetism for their shared perspectives and love for deep atmospheric music leading to the formation of the GMJ & Matter collaboration.
Already drawn by a respect for each others unique sound, their first meeting soon saw them in the studio crafting the acclaimed “Superposition” EP for Proton music, which was debuted at Rainbow Serpent Festival 2016 and released afterwards to big success, supported by industry heavyweights including Hernan Cattaneo and Cid Inc. This was followed by the “Osmosis / 11 moons” EP in 2017, and the “Interscope / To the Stars” EP in 2018 which further highlighted the pair's distinct and accomplished sound.
A natural synergy and seamless understanding has seen works constantly flow, with remixes for Pete K, Andre Sobota, Juan Deminicis, Nopi, Donny Carr, DJ San & Rudy UK, as well as fellow Aussies Funkform, Pantheon and David Leckenby. 2019 raised the bar higher as the duo joined forces with Funkform for a highly anticipated debut EP for the esteemed Balance Music.
Studio success translated into demand from a constantly growing number of respected festivals and clubs both locally and abroad. A debut performance at Dragon Dreaming Festival 2017 was followed soon after with support gigs for Nick Warren and Dezza, leading towards a fully live performance for Wildwood events, then on to their debut European tour in late 2019, with gigs for Progressive Astronaut in London and Replug Records 10 year anniversary at ADE in Amsterdam.
2020 has seen the conception and constant growth of the pairs “Meanwhile Recordings” imprint, which has opened to high regard throughout the industry, both as a platform for their own signature sounds, and as a home to some of the world’s finest. With many amazing artists and releases on the horizon, Meanwhile is already on the way to establishing itself as a premier force in the world of global deep progressive house.

description:
On Thursday, 1 October 2015, we will be celebrating the 25th anniversary of the German reunification in Brussels at the Cinquantenaire – in a spectacular way!

From 19:00 to 24:00, the Triumphal Arch will be treated with a unique sound, light and video show, immersing its fascinating architecture in celebratory colours while renowned DJs from Berlin and major other European cities will spin a crossover of classical and modern electronic music, supervised by the Berlin Dj & Producer Chris Zippel.

Berlin light artist Matthias Zeckert and the internationally renowned video artists ‘Vision Impossible’ from Amsterdam will make for an unforgettable evening! Every hour, an 8-minute video mapping will be projected onto the arch, creating a unique vision of the European story: from divided Europe, to the peaceful revolution in Eastern Europe, German reunification and the process of European integration. Moreover, with powerful images we will show how Germany and its European partners are committed to working closely together to make Europe fit for the future.

In between the video mapping projections, a unique light show will create constantly changing patterns on the beautiful Triumphal Arch and its two wings. DJs Rainer Kranich (Ibiza, 1944-2014), Chris Zippel (Berlin), Rich Ears (Amsterdam), Aiora (Athens) and ED2000 (London) will set the scene for a beautiful evening with their relaxed, ambient music especially compiled for this light show. A range of food and drinks from Germany will be available. Entrance is free.

This once-in-a-lifetime event is organised by the Permanent Representation of the Federal Republic of Germany to the European Union and supported by major German companies, the Goethe Institut, BOZAR and the City of Brussels.

Don’t miss it! Come along with your friends and enjoy a great evening together

My dear friends built up their fire tent which became the center of the Chill Out Area. There I played Saturday Night from 11pm-0.30am, right before Chris Zippel who kindly invited me! Thank you so much for all your enthusiasm, kind words and positive feedback! So much respect and gratitude to Uwe who is the organiser of Antaris for putting all his passion into this project! http://genuinesounds.bandcamp.com/album/still-love-ep


Chris Zippel counts among the most prolific ambient/downtempo artists of the present time… production work with Artists like the Pet Shop Boys, Robbie Williams, Ich und Ich, Snap and just lately Jose Padilla (with whom he just finished on top two remixes for the american Singer Norah Jones), speaks volumes.

His latest original single effort "Still Love", featuring the stand out voice of scandinavian songstress Sophie Tusnelda, creates a deep, unique vibe fuelled by the genuine Zippel trademark sound of course. "Sophie writes those kind of lyrics that come very close to my imagination of perfect melancholy" Chris says - and puts on smile.  

The silky original version of "Still Love" comes alongside three tantalizing remixes on this debut EP for Mole Listening Pearls.  
The Klangstein & Chris Zippel mix adds quite a vital dose of bass heavy downtempo groove to the sensual original - meanwhile, both the Aiora In Dub mix as well as the Chris Zippel & Dimitris Giakoumakis mix aim clearly at the adult dancefloors around the globe.
All that a tasty precursor to the upcoming Chris Zippel album... which incorporates an intense amount of inspiration that the vivid producer has soaked up in & around his new homebase, the white island of Ibiza, throughout the course of the last three years.
